OKLAHOMA GAS AND ELECTRIC COMPANY POWER SALES TARIFF
1.0 Availability
1.1 This Tariff provides for sales of electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services at negotiated rates.
2.0 Rates, Service, and Terms and Conditions of Service
2.1 All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Oklahoma Gas and Electric Company ("OG&E").
2.2 All other terms and conditions of any sale under this Tariff shall be established by agreement between OG&E and purchaser.
3.0 Miscellaneous
3.1 Nothing in this Tariff is intended to create or to imply the existence of any rights hereunder for or on behalf of any third parties.
3.2 OG&E shall have the right to revise, amend, cancel, or terminate this Tariff or a Service Agreement executed hereunder by unilateral filing with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("FERC" or the "Commission"). Nothing contained in this Tariff shall be construed as affecting in any way the ability of any party receiving service hereunder to exercise its rights under the Federal Power Act and pursuant to the FERC's rules and regulations promulgated thereunder.
4.0 Compliance with Commission Regulations
4.1 OG&E shall comply with provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning OG&E's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes OG&E to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits OG&E's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning OG&E's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
5.0 Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority
5.1 N/A
5.2 The Commission originally granted OG&E market-based rate authority in 81 FERC 61,333 (1997), issued in Docket No. ER98-511-000.
6.0 Seller Category
6.1 OG&E is a Category 2 Seller in the Southwest Power Pool region and a Category 1 Seller in all other reporting regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
7.0 Ancillary Services 7.1 SPP: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to Southwest Power Pool, Inc. ("SPP") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
7.2 MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
